## Attribution and Credits

SeedFW is built upon the excellent work of several open-source projects and
methodologies. We are deeply grateful to the following creators:

### PRP (Product Requirement Prompts)
- **Author**: Rasmus Widing
- **Repository**: https://github.com/Wirasm/PRPs-agentic-eng
- **License**: MIT License
- **Contribution**: PRP methodology, context engineering principles, command
  structure, and planning approach
- **Website**: https://www.rasmuswiding.com/
- **Support**: https://coff.ee/wirasm

### OpenSpec
- **Author**: Fission AI
- **Repository**: https://github.com/Fission-AI/OpenSpec
- **License**: MIT License
- **Contribution**: Spec-driven development methodology, change tracking system,
  delta format, and source-of-truth approach
- **Website**: https://fission.ai/

### CyberSun Framework
- **Author**: CyberianSun
- **Repository**: https://github.com/CyberianSun/cybersun-framework
- **License**: MIT License
- **Contribution**: Vertical Slice Architecture, AI operational guidelines,
  file organization principles, and development standards

---

## What SeedFW Adds

While SeedFW is built on these excellent foundations, it adds:

1. **Intent Translator** - Systematic requirement clarification protocol
2. **Unified Workflow** - Combines all three methodologies into one coherent process
3. **Consolidated Commands** - 22 commands instead of 51, no duplicates
4. **GOLDEN_RULES.md** - Unified best practices from all sources
5. **3-Level Validation** - Comprehensive quality assurance
6. **Complete Documentation** - Decision flow, architecture guide, workflow guide

